    "description": {
      "value": "<p>You use Transmutation magic to give your arrow an ethereal quality. When you use this option, you donâ€™t make an Attack roll for the Attack. Instead, the arrow shoots forward in a line, which is 1 foot wide and 30 feet long, before disappearing. The arrow passes harmlessly through Objects, ignoring cover. Each creature in that line must make a <strong>Dexterity saving throw</strong>. On a failed save, a creature takes damage as if it were hit by the arrow, plus an extra <strong>1d6 piercing damage</strong>. On a successful save, a target takes half as much damage.</p>\n<p>The piercing damage increases to <strong>2d6</strong> when you reach 18th level in this class.</p>\n<section class=\"secret\">\n<p><em>Note: After adding this feature to your character, set Resource Consumption to Item Uses: Arcane Shot.</em></p>\n</section>",
